  "notes": "Source is the Exhibit on page 50 'Probability of Retirement' printed as Age rows x Years-of-Service columns, the reverse of the target orientation, so transpose=true. After transpose, printed columns (<15, 15-24, 25-31, >31) become rows mapped to target service buckets, and printed age rows become target age columns. Values are percentages (values_unit=percent). Service bin spans: '<15' -> [null,14], '15-24' -> [15,24], '25-31' -> [25,31], '>31' -> [32,null]. Target buckets 5-11 and 12-19 fall entirely within '<15'; 20-24 within '15-24'; 25-29 and 30 within '25-31'; 31-32 spans 25-31 (year 31) and >31 (year 32) so uses overlap_weighted with both spans; 33-34, 35-39, 40 within '>31'. Age columns: single ages inside a printed age group copy that group's rate; ages inside grouped bins (50-51, 55-58, 66-69) use overlap_weighted with the group's span. Table prints no totals."
